snippet.textDisplay: In my experience (2 and a half years with green hair) the reason Jay's hair turned out so blue, is because a lot of darker green dyes tend to be quite blue based. This works out i the consumer's favour, as they don't have to lighten their hair too much, as they can take advantage of the yelllow tones from when they lightened their hair, and they don't have to lighten it as much as they would have to with pink or purple hair.

snippet.textDisplay: The Arctic Fox Phantom Green has strong blue undertones that will fade to blue. So since she had a more vibrant yellow blonde at the roots, the yellow undertone kept the color a more true vivid green. Her ends were almost white and more porous so I'm thinking it couldn't hold onto the stronger green pigment and showed up as blue, showing us more of what it will fade out to.
snippet.textOriginal: The Arctic Fox Phantom Green has strong blue undertones that will fade to blue. snippet.textDisplay: Not a hair stylist lol but I’ve worked with that phantom green hair dye from Artic Fox. It’s so heavily blue based that if you start with white hair that blue really shows through. For that specific dye it’s better for you to start out with a yellow base to help cancel out the blue undertones in the dye and be left with the deep green that hair dye advertises.
snippet.textOriginal: Not a hair stylist lol but I’ve worked with that phantom green hair dye from Artic Fox. It’s so heavily blue based that if you start with white hair that blue really shows through. For that specific dye it’s better for you to start out with a yellow base to help cancel out the blue undertones in the dye and be left with the deep green that hair dye advertises.

snippet.textDisplay: @BradMondo so as professional I can tell you the blue thing is very common with overprocessed hair. Most semi-permanent colors are ment to be done on level 8 hair which is yellowish. The blue pigments are stronger in green color so they can mix the the existing yellow pigment of the hair to create green. If the hair is lifted too much the hair will show up blue instead of green. Hope this answered your question.
